		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, Super NES can't do hi-res sprites. That's why my own Pygame projects (<a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=109649#p109649" class="postlink">Wrecking Ball Boy</a> and <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=112810#p112810" class="postlink">FHBG remake</a>) render to an offscreen Surface 256 pixels wide and upscale that to the screen.

		

