		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Someone began working on a python compiler for NES:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://github.com/gutomaia/pyNES">https://github.com/gutomaia/pyNES</a><!-- m --><br /><br />I personally never got it to install or compile correctly but maybe someone familiar with Python (you) could use it.  Still would have to write your own routines or reimplement what you used from pygame but it'd be a REAL NES game <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
