		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">slobu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Someone began working on a python compiler for NES:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://github.com/gutomaia/pyNES">https://github.com/gutomaia/pyNES</a><!-- m --></div><br />It's not really a compiler. It's just a cute hack where the (Python) code that you write actually generates 6502 assembly through the library routines that are called. This approach is severely limited.

		

